body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, my name is Jonathan Morris and I'm a customer service representative at Auto Experts Inc.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: May I please have your name?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi there, my name is Crystal Rodriguez.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Crystal. Can you provide me with your mobile phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my number is seven eight six five five five one two three four.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Crystal. I also need your email address. Could you please share that with me?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email address is c dot rod at example dot com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Crystal. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Not at the moment, thank you.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Crystal. Have a great day!
